	</div>
</div> <!-- /home-banner -->

<div class="hp-topper-intro holiday-bg ">
	<div class="portfolio-h-outer">
		<div class="portfolio-h-inner">
			<h1 class="txt-lg hp-intro-txt">Happy Holidays from Upstatement!  We’d like to share with you a behind-the-scenes look at the making of our holiday gift set.</h1>
		</div><!-- /portfolio-h-inner -->
	</div><!-- /portfolio-h-outer -->
</div><!-- /hp-topper-intro -->

<section class="hp-themes home-inset holiday-bg">
		<div class="wrapper">
			<div class="hp-theme-alt">
				<div class="tiles-mod">

					<div class="tile-row-mod">
						<div class="alt-tile tile-border no-border ui-block-1">

							<a href="/happy-holidays/holiday-card-2012"><img class="alt-tile-img" src="/wp-content/themes/blades/images/holiday-100-years.jpg" alt="Celebrating 100 Years"/></a>
							<h2 class="highlight-headline"><a href="/happy-holidays/holiday-card-2012">An Upstatement Tradition</a></h2>
							<div class="txt-lg txt-dark">
								<p>We’re excited to not only keep <a href="http://upstatement.com/happy-holidays/holiday-card-2012">this tradition</a> alive but thrilled to have expanded upon the concept of the holiday card and included 100 handmade gift boxes into the mix. We also take pride in the fact that every component was printed locally and made-by-hand here in Boston!</p>
							</div><!-- /txt-lg -->
						</div> <!-- /alt-tile -->

						<div class="alt-tile tile-border ui-block-2">
							<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/boston_public_library/sets/72157625033396759/"><img class="alt-tile-img" src="/wp-content/themes/blades/images/hc-wharf.jpg" alt="Upstatement Tradition"/></a>
							<h2 class="highlight-headline"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/boston_public_library/sets/72157625033396759/">Celebrating 100 Years</a></h2>
							<div class="txt-lg txt-dark">
								<p>The inspiration for our holiday card was found right here at Upstatement HQ. Our home in Boston's Fort Point neighborhood at 319 A Street, is celebrating its 100th Birthday this year! Our web design dojo graces the front of this year’s card and the coaster set shares views from our neighborhood from the turn of the century.</p>
							</div><!-- /txt-lg -->
						</div> <!-- /alt-tile -->
					</div> <!-- /tile-row-mod -->

				</div> <!-- /tiles-mod -->
			</div> <!-- /hp-theme-alt -->
		</div> <!-- /wrapper -->
</section> <!-- /hp-themes -->

<div class="hp-logo-pond holiday-pond">
